<h1> Markdown syntax demo</h1>

<h2> Headings start with #</h2>

<p>
this is a paragraph
we are on the same paragraph
</p>

<p>
new paragraph here
</p>

<h2> Inline formatting</h2>

<p>
<b>bold</b>
</p>

<p>
<i>italic</i>
</p>

<p>
<code>monospace</code>
</p>

<p>
superscript: hello<sup>world</sup>
</p>

<p>
subscript: H<sub>2</sub>O
</p>

<h2> Lists</h2>

<p>
unordered lists
</p>
<ul>
<li><p>first</p></li>
<li><p>second</p>
<ul>
<li><p>nested list</p></li>
<li><p>second</p></li>
</ul>
nested paragraph</p>
<ul>
<li><p>another nest</p>
<ul>
<li><p>more nesting</p>
<ul>
<li><p>even more</p></li>
</ul>
</p></li>
</ul>
</p></li>
<li><p>more symbols</p></li>
<li><p>even more</p></li>
</ul>
</p></li>
<li><p>third</p></li>
</ul>

<p>
ordered lists
</p>
<ol start='1'>
<li><p>first</p></li>
<li><p>second</p>
<ol start='4'>
<li><p>nested list (starting number is preserved)</p></li>
<li><p>second</p>
<ol start='111'>
<li><p>more nesting</p>
<ol start='1'>
<li><p>even more</p></li>
</ol>
</p></li>
</ol>
</p></li>
</ol>
</p></li>
<li><p>third</p></li>
</ol>

<h2> Maths</h2>

<p>
write latex between dollar signs
</p>

<p>
inline math: \(x^2 - y^2 = (x+y)(x-y)\)
</p>

<p>
block math:
</p>
\[
\frac{d}{dx} f(x) = \lim_{h \to 0} \frac{f(x+h) - f(x)}{h}
\]
<h2> Code blocks</h2>
<pre>
#include &lt;stdio.h&gt;

int main() {
    puts("Hello world");
}
</pre>
